rs consider politicians as both cause and effect. Drawing on pioneering field research on the opinions of Latin American legislators in 17 countries, they focus on two broad topics: political systems, as reflected in politicians' perspectives on the democracies and party organizations of which they are a part; and the role played by ideology, not only in shaping positions on issues, but also as a factor that gives coherence to parties. Their seminal work is central to the current political dynamics in the region, as well as to broader debates in political science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aLegislative bodiesxLatin America. 0aLegislative bodieszLatin America. 0aPolitical partiesxLatin America. 0aPolitical partieszLatin America. 0aPoliticiansxLatin AmericaxLatin America. 0aPoliticianszLatin America. 0aRepresentative government and representationxLatin America. 0aRepresentative government and representationzLatin America. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh1 aAlcántara Sáez, Manuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreidenberg, Flavia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía Díez, Fátima, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía Montero, Mercedes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLlamazares Valduvieco, Iván, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarenghi, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartí i Puig, Salvador, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartínez Rosón, María del Mar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMateos Díaz, Araceli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rel